    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-29T19:33:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-29T19:33:00-05:00" n="371"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">689.90D/11–2951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Afghanistan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-29T19:33:00-05:00"
                            >December 29, 1951—7:33 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>206. Dept in accord desirability certain econ objectives and their relationship
                        <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss>–Afghan relations advanced <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 260 Nov 29. However Dept questions
                    whether <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> wld be inclined actively to
                    cooperate in improvement Afghan econ position in absence demonstration good
                    faith <gloss target="#t_GOA1">GOA</gloss>. Such demonstration not yet
                    forthcoming except decrease local press propaganda which not as significant as
                    radio propaganda that reaches <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> audience.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> re para 2 your memo conversation des 187 Dec
                    3 there are no funds available this <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> for grant
                    aid to Kabul Kandahar highway project and Dept cannot now predict level <gloss
                        target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> appropriation <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss>
                    1953. Hence in conversations with <gloss target="#t_GOA1">GOA</gloss> Emb shld
                    carefully avoid statements that may lead Afghans expect more than Dept can
                    offer.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
